The regression of the corpus luteum is essential to reset the ovarian cycle, so that mammals obtain another chance to become pregnant.

definition.value: A partial displacement (or dislocation) of the lens is described as lens subluxation, while a complete displacement is termed lens luxation.

value.value: 水晶体脱臼
complete displacement of the crystalline lens of the eye out of its normal position
The lens is defined as luxated (dislocated) when it lies completely outside of the hyaloid fossa, is free-floating in the vitreous, is in the anterior chamber, or lies directly on the retina.
レンズ亜脱臼
partial displacement of the crystalline lens of the eye out of its normal position
The lens is considered subluxated when it is partially displaced but remains within the lens space.

definition.value: This term should be used when there is a physiological anomaly in the ability to create a copulatory plug but mating behavior is normal
